DescriptiveText: NA

Name: Detrended Elevation SD
DescriptiveText: Standard Deviation of all cells for the detrended DEM.

Name: Thalweg Depth CV
DescriptiveText: Retired metric.  Coefficient of Variation (CV) of thalweg depths at a site.  Filtering has been removed and metric is now the same as DpthThwg_CV.

Name: Wetted Depth SD
DescriptiveText: Standard Deviation of water depths within the wetted channel.

Name: Sinuosity
DescriptiveText: Ratio of the thalweg length to the straight line distance between the start and end points of the thalweg.

Name: Sinuosity Via Centerline
DescriptiveText: Ratio of the wetted centerline length (Site Length Wetted) and the straight line distance between the start and end points of the wetted centerline. Generated by the River Bathymetry Toolkit (RBT)

Name: Wetted Channel Island Count
DescriptiveText: The total number of islands in the wetted polygon.

Name: Wetted Channel Qualifying Island Area
DescriptiveText: The total area of all qualifying islands in the wetted polygon.

Name: Wetted Channel Qualifying Island Count
DescriptiveText: The number of qualifying islands in the wetted polygon.

Name: Wetted Channel Braidedness
DescriptiveText: Ratio of the total length of the wetted mainstem channel plus side channels and the length of the mainstem channel.

Name: Wetted Channel Mainstem Sinuosity
DescriptiveText: Length of the wetted main channel divided by the straight line length between the top and bottom endpoints of the wetted main channel centerline.

Name: Wetted Side Channel Percent By Area
DescriptiveText: Ratio of the total area of side channel unit areas (both small and large) divided by the total area of channel unit polygons.

Name: Wetted Large Side Channel Area
DescriptiveText: Sum of the large side channel unit areas.

Name: Wetted Small Side Channel Area
DescriptiveText: Sum of all small side channel unit areas at a site.

Name: Wetted Side Channel Width to Depth Ratio Avg
DescriptiveText: Average wetted width to depth ratio of qualifying side channels measured from from cross-sections.  Depths represent the average depth of 10 stations along each cross-section.

Name: Wetted Side Channel Width to Depth Ratio CV
DescriptiveText: Coefficient of variation of qualifying wetted side channel width to average depth ratios measured from cross sections.

Name: Wetted Side Channel Width
DescriptiveText: Average wetted width of side channel(s)  measured from cross-sections.

Name: Wetted Side Channel Width CV
DescriptiveText: Coefficient of Variation of qualifying side channel wetted widths measured from cross-sections.

Name: Wetted Side Channel Width to Max Depth Ratio Avg
DescriptiveText: Average wetted width to max depth ratio of qualifying side channels measured from cross-sections. Depths represent the max depth of 10 stations along each cross-section.

Name: Wetted Side Channel Width to Max Depth Ratio CV
DescriptiveText: Coefficient of variation of  qualifying wetted width to max depth ratios of side channels measured from cross-sections.

Name: Wetted Width To Depth Ratio Avg
DescriptiveText: Average width to depth ratio of the wetted channel measured from cross-sections. Depths represent an average of depths along each cross-section.

Name: Wetted Width To Depth Ratio CV
DescriptiveText: Retired. Coefficient of Variation of wetted width to depth ratios derived from cross-sections.

Name: Wetted Width CV
DescriptiveText: Coefficient of Variation of the wetted channel width measured from cross-sections.

Name: Wetted Width to Max Depth Ratio Avg
DescriptiveText: Average width to depth ratios of the wetted channel measured from cross-sections. Depth represents the maximum depth along a cross-section.
column17: Average width to depth ratios of the wetted channel measured from average width and max depth of each channel unit.

Name: Wetted Width to Max Depth Ratio CV
DescriptiveText: Coefficient of Variation of width to depth ratios of the wetted channel measured from cross-sections. Depth represents the maximum depth along a cross-section.
column17: Coefficient of Variation of width to depth ratios of the wetted channel measured from average width and max depth of each channel unit.

Name: GCD Avg Net Thickness Diff within Area of Detectable Change For T0: Error
DescriptiveText: The propogated error (m^3) from erosion and deposition cells within the area of interest for T0.

Name: GCD Avg Net Thickness Diff within Area of Detectable Change For T-1: Error
DescriptiveText: The propogated error (m^3) from erosion and deposition cells within the area of interest for T-1.

Name: GCD Avg Net Thickness Diff within Area of Detectable Change For T0
DescriptiveText: Average net thickness of difference between the current visit and first  year of sampling (T0) within the area of detectable change, which is the area where there was detectable change within the union of all bankfull areas for all visits.

Name: GCD Avg Net Thickness Diff within Area of Detectable Change For T-1
DescriptiveText: Average net thickness of difference between the current visit and the last sampling visit (T-1) within the area of detectable change, which is the area where there was detectable change within the union of all bankfull areas for all visits.

Name: GCD Avg Total Thickness Diff within Area of Detectable Change For T0: Error
DescriptiveText: The propogated error (m^3) from erosion and deposition cells within the area of detectable change for T0.

Name: GCD Avg Total Thickness Diff within Area of Detectable Change For T0
DescriptiveText: Average thickness of difference between the current visit and first  year of sampling (T0) within the area of detectable change, which is the area where there was detectable change within the union of all bankfull areas for all visits.

Name: GCD Avg Total Thickness Diff within Area of Detectable Change For T-1
DescriptiveText: Average thickness of difference between the current visit and most recent year of sampling (T-1) within the area of detectable change, which is the area where there was detectable change within the union of all bankfull areas for all visits.

Name: GCD Percent of Area of Interest with Detectable Change For T0
DescriptiveText: The percent of the total area of interest with detectable changes (i.e. either exceeding the minimum level of detection or with a proability greater then the confidence interval chosen by user) from current visit to earliest visit to the site (T0).

Name: GCD Percent of Area of Interest with Detectable Change For T-1
DescriptiveText: The percent of the total area of interest with detectable changes (i.e. either exceeding the minimum level of detection or with a proability greater then the confidence interval chosen by user) from current visit to the last visit to the site (T-1).

Name: GCD Avg Net Thickness Diff within Area of Interest For T0: Error

DescriptiveText: The propogated error (m^3) from erosion and deposition cells within the area of interest for T-1.

DescriptiveText: The propogated error (m^3) from erosion and deposition cells within the area of interest for T0.

Name: GCD Avg Total Thickness Diff within Area of Interest For T-1
DescriptiveText: Average total thickness of difference between the current visit and most recent year of sampling (T-1) within the area of interest, which is the union of all bankfull areas for all visits.

Name: GCD Percent Net Volume Ratio for T0
DescriptiveText: The ratio of net volumetric change to the total volume of change between the current visit and the first visit to the site (T0).

Name: GCD Percent Net Volume Ratio for T-1
DescriptiveText: The ratio of net volumetric change to the total volume of change between the current visit and the first visit to the site (T-1).

Name: GCD Percent Imbalance For T0

Name: GCD Percent Imbalance For T-1

DescriptiveText: Site water surface gradient is calculated as the difference between the top of site (upstream) and bottom of site (downstream) water surface elevations divided by thalweg length.

DescriptiveText: The total length of the bankfull centerline derived from the bankfull polygon.

DescriptiveText: Total length of the main channel and all side channels at bankfull.

DescriptiveText: The total length of the thalweg at a site.

DescriptiveText: Length of the main wetted channel.

Name: Mean Annual Flow
DescriptiveText: Mean daily flow, averaged over a year. Also sometimes called mean annual flow. Units: cubic feet per second (cfs).

Name: Residual Pool Depth
DescriptiveText: The average difference between the maximum depth and downstream end depth of all Slow Water/Pool channel units.

Name: Precipitation
DescriptiveText: The 103 year average of precipitation for a given point from PRISM data.

Name: Discharge
DescriptiveText: The sum of station discharge across all  stations.  Station discharge is calculated as depth x velocity x station increment for all stations except first and last.  Station discharge for first and last station is 0.5 x station width x depth x velocity.

DescriptiveText: NA

Name: 7dAMGtr12
DescriptiveText: Number of 7-day average of daily maximum (7dAM) values between July 15th and August 31st that are greater than 12°C.  Relates to bull trout spawning and juvenile rearing.

Name: 7dAMGtr13
DescriptiveText: Number of 7-day average of daily maximum (7dAM) values between July 15th and August 31st that are greater than 13°C.  Relates to salmon and steelhead spawning.

Name: 7dAMGtr16
DescriptiveText: Number of 7-day average of daily maximum (7dAM) values between July 15th and August 31st that are greater than 16°C.  Relates to suitability as core cold water habitat.

Name: 7dAMGtr18
DescriptiveText: Number of 7-day average of daily maximum (7dAM) values between July 15th and August 31st that are greater than 18°C.  Relates to salmon and trout rearing and migration.

Name: 7dAMGtr20
DescriptiveText: Number of 7-day average of daily maximum (7dAM) values between July 15th and August 31st that are greater than 20°C.  Relates to salmon and steelhead migration.

Name: 7dAMGtr22
DescriptiveText: Number of 7-day average of daily maximum (7dAM) values between July 15th and August 31st that are greater than 22°C.  Indicates if temperatures create a thermal barrier to salmonid migration.

Name: SummerHourlyAverageTemp
DescriptiveText: Average of all hourly temperature measurements collected July 15th - August 31st.

Name: Max7dAM
DescriptiveText: Highest 7-day average of daily maximum (7dAM) value between July 15th - August 31st.
